go_data.justification: c-ret is activated as a tyrosine kinase upon binding to GFR-alpha1.
Secreted GDNF binds to GFR-alpha1, resulting in activation of the c-ret tyrosine kinase, which controls ingrowth of the ureteric bud.
As a receptor tyrosine kinase, c-ret is embedded in the cell surface to interact with its ligand.
